17/02/2008
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- A new political was established on Saturday (February 16th). The United People's Party (ENP) adopted its charter at a constituent congress in the presence of more than 500 delegates. Independent parliament member Maria Capon was elected leader of the party. The ENP declared it will be committed to legal state principles, justice and freedom. The party also said it will work for the establishment of a free market in Bulgaria and will support Euro-Atlantic security and solidarity. (BGNES, Actualno - 16/02/08)
